# Step 0
# Follow the directions for configuring configuring a JMS or InMem adapter located in examples/README
# Perform steps 1-3 in separate terminals

# Step 1
# Start up the application
rm -f modern_times.yml
rackup -p 4567

# Step 2
# Browse to http://localhost:4567
# Open up the tree to ModernTimes => Bar => Attributes
# Enter 2 for count and click the Update button.
# Open up the tree to ModernTimes => Baz => Attributes
# Enter 3 for count and click the Update button.

# Step 3
# Publish 10 messages to the BarWorker and 5 to the BazWorker
jruby publish.rb 10 5

# Step 4
# cntl-c the rackup process and start it back up.  It should come back with
# the workers that have been configured via the browser
# Browse to http://localhost:4567/ModernTimes/Bar/timer/attributes.json?reset=true
# You could poll this url to create a graph or alert for your system using some monitoring
# software such as munin, nagios, or hyperic.

